definition.value: A state in central northern Nigeria. Its capital is Dutse. Kano State and Katsina State border Jigawa to the west, Bauchi State to the east and Yobe State to the northeast. To the north, Jigawa shares an international border with Zinder Region in The Republic of Niger.
A state in central northern Nigeria. Its capital is Kaduna.

A state located in North-Western Nigeria. Created on 1967-05-27 from part of the Northern Region, Kano state borders Katsina State to the north-west, Jigawa State to the north-east, and Bauchi and Kaduna states to the south. The capital of Kano State is Kano.
A state in northern Nigeria. Its capital is Katsina. In 1987, Katsina State was formed from part of Kaduna State.
A state located in northeastern Nigeria. Created in 2004-10-01 1996 from part of the old Bauchi State.
A state of Nigeria, located in the southwestern part of the country. Lagos State is divided into 5 Administrative divisions, which are further divided into 37 Local Government Areas.
A state of Nigeria. Its capital is Ilorin. Kwara State was created on 1967-05-27.
A state in the north-central zone of Nigeria. The state was formed in 1991 from parts of Kwara State and Benue State.

A state in central Nigeria. Its capital is Lafia. Nasarawa State is bounded in the north by Kaduna State, in the west by the Federal Capital Territory, in the south by Kogi and Benue States and in the east by Taraba and Plateau States.

A state in north-western Nigeria with its capital at Birnin Kebbi. The state was formed from part of Sokoto State in 1991. Kebbi State is bordered by Sokoto State, Niger State, Dosso Region in the Republic of Niger and the nation of Benin.
A state of Nigeria. Created on 1976-02-03 from the former Western State. It originally included what is now Ekiti State, which was split off in 1996. Akure is the state capital.
An inland state in southwestern Nigeria and home to several of Nigeria's most famous landmarks, including the campus of Obafemi Awolowo University.
A state in South-western Nigeria. It borders Lagos State to the South, Oyo and Osun states to the North, Ondo State to the east and the republic of Benin to the west.
A state in the western part of Nigeria. It was formed in 1976 when the then North-Western State was bifurcated into Niger State and Sokoto State.
A state in north-western Nigeria.

A state located in Northern Nigeria. The capital of Yobe state is Damaturu. The state borders the Nigerian states of Bauchi, Borno, Gombe, and Jigawa. It borders Diffa Region and Zinder Region to the north in The Republic of Niger.
A state of Nigeria. Taraba State is bounded in the west by Plateau and Benue States and on the east by the Cameroon.
A state in northwestern Nigeria. Its capital is Gusau.

A state of Nigeria. Its capital is Port Harcourt. It is bounded on the South by the Atlantic Ocean, to the North by Imo and Abia States, to the East by Akwa Ibom State and to the West by Bayelsa and Delta states. The state was formed in 1967 with the split of the Eastern Region of Nigeria. Until 1996 the state contained the area which is now in the Bayelsa State.
A region in Senegal.
The southwest region of the northern part of Senegal.
A region located to the northwest part of Senegal.
A region in Senegal. It borders Gambia.
Not found.
The smallest and most populated region of Senegal, encompassing the capital city of the country, Dakar, and all its suburbs along the Cape Verde Peninsula, Africa's most westerly point.
A region of Senegal.
A region of Senegal sits just off the border with Mauritania. Capital: Saint-Louis.
A region of western Senegal.
A region in the SE of Senegal.
A region located to the NE part of Senegal. It is bounded on the north by the Senegal River and the south by the Sahelian plain.

One of four principal divisions of Sierra Leone. It comprises the oldest city and national capital Freetown and its surrounding suburbs. To the northeast, the Western Area borders the Northern Province, and to the southeast it borders the Southern Province. However, most of the boundaries of the Western Area is the shoreline of the Atlantic Ocean.
One of three provinces of Sierra Leone.
One of the three provinces of Sierra Leone.
One of the three provinces of Sierra Leone.
One of the five administrative divisions of The Gambia.

The capital of The Gambia, and located within the division of the same name. It is located on Saintt Mary's Island (Banjul Island) where the Gambia River enters the Atlantic Ocean. The island is connected to the mainland by passenger and vehicle ferries to the north and bridges to the south.
The largest of the five administrative divisions of The Gambia. Its capital is Janjanbureh (formerly Georgetown), on MacCarthy Island.
One of the five administrative divisions of The Gambia. Its capital is Kerewan.
One of the five administrative divisions of The Gambia. Its capital is Basse Santa Su.
One of the five administrative divisions of The Gambia. Its capital is Brikama.
One of the five administrative divisions of The Gambia. Its capital is Mansa Konko.
The southernmost of Togo's five regions, with the country's only shoreline on the Bight of Benin.
One of Togo's five regions. Kara is the regional capital.
One of Togo's five regions.
The northernmost of the five Regions of Togo. Dapaong is the regional capital.
One of Togo's five regions. Sokode is the regional capital.
A region in southwest Iceland.
A region in the N of Iceland.
A region in the E of Iceland.
